Combine 3 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon sherry, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt in medium bowl; add meat and marinate 1 hour. Combine remaining soy sauce, sherry, sugar and salt with beef broth, vinegar and pepper flakes. Dissolve cornstarch in mixture; set aside. Heat oil over high heat in skillet or wok. Add meat, garlic and ginger. Stir-fry about 2 minutes. Add bell pepper, water chestnuts and green onions; continue cooking 1 minute. Add cornstarch mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent. Serve over rice, if desired.